-- Mitsui unit gets $1.9 billion bill from BP for clean-up
-- 
-- Tue Nov 2, 2010 3:22am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2010/11/02/us-mitsui-spill-idUSTRE6A10NU20101102

 

 TOKYO  (Reuters) - A Mitsui & Co unit said on Tuesday that it received a bill for about $1.9 billion from BP Plc to help with the clean-up of the Gulf of Mexico oil spill. 

 Mitsui Oil Exploration Co also said in a statement it was withholding the payment while it continued to examine the issue. (Reporting by Yuko Inoue)